{"updated_at": "2013-07-09T13:52:00Z", "repo": "rails", "created_at": "2013-07-09T13:52:00Z", "owner": "rails", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/20675021", "id": 20675021, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/3946", "issue_id": 3946, "user": {"repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/botimer/repos", "type": "User", "html_url": "https://github.com/botimer", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/botimer/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/botimer/subscriptions", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/botimer/following{/other_user}", "gravatar_id": "48781c2a99785b4afaf80471af8b6ddc", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/botimer/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/botimer", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/botimer/gists{/gist_id}", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/48781c2a99785b4afaf80471af8b6ddc?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fa57807c81690eb3f15132aef4d618544.png", "id": 159019, "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/botimer/events{/privacy}", "login": "botimer", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/botimer/received_events", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/botimer/followers"}, "body": "I am seeing on Rails 3.2.13 that `config.assets.initialize_on_precompile = false` causes `config.relative_url_root` to be omitted in compiled assets.\r\n\r\nHowever, `RAILS_RELATIVE_URL_ROOT` from the environment is being applied to `config.relative_url_root` as expected. (You can also clearly set this manually.)\r\n\r\nAs mentioned above, `config.action_controller.relative_url_root` is the parameter that applies to the asset paths, so I have added one line to `production.rb` to restore the expected behavior:\r\n\r\n~~~\r\nconfig.action_controller.relative_url_root = config.relative_url_root\r\n~~~", "_id": {"$oid": "52382f63bd3543c15100f535"}, "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/3946#issuecomment-20675021"}
